For each integer \( k \) from 0 to 20, the set of points where \(|x| + |y| = k\) forms a diamond with vertices at \((k, 0)\), \((0, k)\), \((-k, 0)\), and \((0, -k)\). To count the number of such points: 1. For \( k = 0 \), the only point is \((0, 0)\), contributing 1 point. 2. For each \( k \) from 1 to 20, the number of points on the layer \(|x| + |y| = k\) is \(4k\).
